# Part I — Minor Project (Completed ✅)

## 1. Project Overview

**Axion** is a vendor-neutral, event-driven Electric Vehicle (EV) Fleet Telemetry, Digital Twin, and OTA Orchestration Platform. It ingests, normalizes, and processes EV telemetry at scale, maintains real-time digital twins for each vehicle, computes explainable health indicators, and orchestrates over-the-air (OTA) update simulations.

The system is designed to tolerate unreliable vehicle connectivity, heterogeneous vendor data formats, and high-throughput telemetry streams — providing operators with actionable fleet insights.

### Core Objectives Achieved
- ✅ Ingest telemetry from multiple vehicles using REST and MQTT protocols
- ✅ Normalize vendor-specific data into a canonical internal schema
- ✅ Maintain a real-time digital twin per vehicle in Redis
- ✅ Compute explainable vehicle health scores (0–100)
- ✅ Simulate safe, controlled OTA update rollouts
- ✅ Provide fleet-level and vehicle-level analytics dashboard
- ✅ Python-based multi-vehicle simulator with fault injection

---

## 2. System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    SIM["🐍 Python Simulator<br/>250 Vehicles, 5 Scenarios"]
    REST["REST API<br/>/api/v1/telemetry"]
    MQTT["MQTT Broker<br/>Eclipse Mosquitto"]
    
    SIM -->|HTTP POST| REST
    SIM -->|MQTT Publish| MQTT
    
    REST --> ING["Spring Boot<br/>Ingestion Service"]
    MQTT --> ING
    
    ING -->|Normalize + Validate| KAFKA["Apache Kafka<br/>telemetry.normal"]
    
    KAFKA --> CONSUMER["TelemetryConsumer"]
    CONSUMER --> TWIN["Digital Twin Service"]
    TWIN --> REDIS["Redis<br/>Live State, 120s TTL"]
    
    REDIS --> API["Fleet REST API"]
    API --> FRONTEND["React Dashboard<br/>Polling 3-5s"]
    
    KAFKA --> OTA_TOPIC["Kafka: ota.events"]
    OTA_TOPIC --> OTA_CONSUMER["OTA Consumer"]
```

### Data Flow Pipeline
```
Python Simulator ──REST/MQTT──► Spring Boot Ingestion
                                       │
                               Validate + Normalize
                                       │
                                       ▼
                             Kafka (telemetry.normal)
                                       │
                                       ▼
                              TelemetryConsumer
                                       │
                           ┌───────────┼───────────┐
                           ▼                       ▼
                    Digital Twin              Health Score
                    (Redis, 120s TTL)         Engine
                           │
                           ▼
                    React Frontend (Polling 3-5s)
```

