## 4. Backend Architecture (Spring Boot)

### 4.1 Ingestion Layer (48 Java Source Files)

The backend follows a clean, layered architecture:

| Package | Purpose | Key Classes |
|---------|---------|-------------|
| `adapter` | Vendor data normalization | `RestTelemetryAdapter`, `TelemetryAdapter` |
| `api` | REST controllers | `FleetController`, `VehicleController` |
| `config` | Infrastructure configuration | `KafkaConsumerConfig`, `KafkaProducerConfig`, `MqttConfig`, `RedisConfig`, `WebConfig` |
| `consumer` | Kafka event processing | `TelemetryConsumer` |
| `controller` | Additional REST endpoints | `OtaController`, `TelemetryIngestionController` |
| `dto` | API response models | `DigitalTwinResponse`, `FleetSummaryResponse`, `FleetVehicleResponse` |
| `exception` | Error handling | `GlobalExceptionHandler`, `InvalidPayloadException`, `ValidationException` |
| `health` | Health scoring engine | [HealthScoreEngine](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Backend/ingestion/src/main/java/com/axion/ingestion/health/HealthScoreEngine.java#11-79), `HealthRules`, `HealthScoreResult`, `HealthState` |
| `model` | Core domain models | `CanonicalTelemetryEnvelope`, `DigitalTwinState`, `TelemetrySnapshot`, `ConnectionMetadata` |
| `mqtt` | MQTT message handling | `MqttMessageHandler` |
| `producer` | Kafka event publishing | `TelemetryKafkaProducer` |
| `service` | Business logic | [DigitalTwinService](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Backend/ingestion/src/main/java/com/axion/ingestion/service/DigitalTwinService.java#14-71), [OtaService](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Backend/ingestion/src/main/java/com/axion/ingestion/service/OtaService.java#12-62), [TelemetryIngestionService](file:///c:/CipherVault/Code/Projects/Axion%20-%20EV%20Fleet%20Management/Axion-Backend/ingestion/src/main/java/com/axion/ingestion/service/TelemetryIngestionService.java#10-33), `ThroughputTracker` |
| `validation` | Payload validation | `TelemetryValidator` |

### 4.2 OTA Module

| Package | Purpose | Key Classes |
|---------|---------|-------------|
| `ota.api` | OTA REST controller | `OtaController` |
| `ota.config` | Kafka config for OTA | `KafkaConfig` |
| `ota.consumer` | OTA event processing | `OtaEventConsumer` |
| `ota.model` | OTA domain models | `OtaCampaign`, `OtaJob`, `OtaState` |
| `ota.producer` | OTA event publishing | `OtaEventProducer` |
| `ota.service` | OTA orchestration | `OtaOrchestratorService` |

### 4.3 Key Features Implemented

**Telemetry Ingestion Service**
- Dual-protocol ingestion (REST + MQTT)
- Adapter pattern converts raw vendor data → `CanonicalTelemetryEnvelope`
- Validation with graceful error handling
- Publishes normalized telemetry to Kafka `telemetry.normal` topic
- Throughput tracking (events/second)

**Digital Twin Service**
- Maintains one authoritative Redis digital twin per vehicle
- Stale data protection using timestamp ordering
- Automatic health score evaluation on each update
- 120-second Redis TTL for twin expiry
- Stores: vehicle ID, vendor, telemetry snapshot, health score, health state, online status

**Health Score Engine**
- Rule-based scoring system (0–100 scale)
- Base score with penalty deductions
- Factors: Battery SOC, battery temperature, connectivity status
- Health states: `HEALTHY` (≥80), `DEGRADED` (50–79), `CRITICAL` (<50)
- Human-readable explanations for each score deduction

**OTA Update Service**
- Health-gated OTA: refuses updates if battery low or temperature high
- Simulated success/failure with 80% success probability
- OTA eligibility tracking per vehicle
- Campaign-based triggering

### 4.4 REST API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/v1/telemetry` | Ingest telemetry (REST) |
| `GET` | `/api/v1/fleet/summary` | Fleet-wide KPIs |
| `GET` | `/api/v1/fleet/vehicles` | All vehicles with telemetry |
| `GET` | `/api/v1/fleet/vehicle/{id}` | Single vehicle digital twin |
| `POST` | `/api/v1/ota/trigger` | Trigger OTA update |

