## 11. Phase-by-Phase Roadmap (10 Weeks)

### Phase 1 — Database & Persistence (Weeks 1–3)

**Goal**: Axion remembers everything — historical telemetry + relational business data.

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| TimescaleDB | PostgreSQL extension | Store millions of telemetry rows with automatic time-partitioning |
| PostgreSQL | Relational DB | Users, OTA campaigns, vehicle policies, audit logs |
| Flyway | Migration tool | Schema version control |

**Key Deliverables**:
- `telemetry_history` hypertable with vehicle-specific indexes
- PostgreSQL tables: `users`, `ota_campaigns`, `ota_jobs`, `vehicle_policies`, `audit_logs`
- Historical telemetry API: time-range queries, hourly aggregates
- 30-day retention policy with auto-cleanup
- Frontend: historical charts (24h / 7d / 30d trends)

---

### Phase 2 — Authentication & Security (Weeks 3–4)

**Goal**: Role-based access control — Admin vs Operator.

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| Spring Security | JWT (HS256, 24h expiry) | Backend authentication |
| BCrypt | Password hashing | Secure credential storage |
| AuthContext | React Context | Frontend auth state management |

**Key Deliverables**:
- JWT-based authentication filter chain
- Role-based endpoint access (ADMIN: full, OPERATOR: read-only)
- Login/Register API endpoints
- Frontend login page, protected routes, conditional UI rendering
- Audit log: "who did what" tracking

---

### Phase 3 — Real-Time WebSockets (Weeks 4–5)

**Goal**: Replace polling with server-push — instant dashboard updates.

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| STOMP over SockJS | Spring WebSocket | Real-time server-to-client push |
| STOMP.js | Frontend library | WebSocket client with auto-reconnect |

**Key Deliverables**:
- WebSocket topics: `/topic/fleet/updates`, `/topic/vehicle/{vehicleId}`
- Message types: `TWIN_UPDATE`, `HEALTH_CHANGE`, `OTA_STATUS`, `ALERT`
- Zero-polling dashboard — all `setInterval` loops replaced
- Toast notifications on health state changes
- Connection status indicator (Connected / Reconnecting)

---

### Phase 4 — ML Predictive Analytics (Weeks 5–8) ⭐

**Goal**: The "star feature" — AI-powered battery degradation prediction and anomaly detection.

| Model | Input | Output |
|-------|-------|--------|
| **Battery Depletion Predictor** | SOC drain rate, speed, temperature | Predicted hours until SOC ≤15% + confidence |
| **Temperature Anomaly Detector** | Temperature trajectory, ambient temp | Anomaly risk (LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH) + predicted peak |

**Stack**: Python 3.11, FastAPI, scikit-learn, XGBoost, pandas

**Key Deliverables**:
- FastAPI microservice (`Axion-ML/`) with trained models
- Prediction endpoints: `/ml/v1/predict/{vehicleId}/battery`, `/ml/v1/predict/{vehicleId}/temperature`
- Fleet risk ranking: `/ml/v1/fleet/risk-ranking`
- Model retraining endpoint
- Spring Boot ML client with Redis caching (60s TTL)
- Frontend: prediction widgets, risk heatmap, ML-driven auto-alerts

---

### Phase 5 — Advanced OTA Orchestration (Weeks 6–8)

**Goal**: Production-grade OTA with canary deployments, health-gating, and automatic rollback.

**Campaign Lifecycle**:
```
DRAFT ──► CANARY ──► ROLLOUT ──► COMPLETED
                  │            │
                  └──► HALTED ◄┘
```

**Key Deliverables**:
- Full campaign lifecycle state machine (persisted in PostgreSQL)
- Canary deployment: 2–3 vehicles → 5-min health check → full rollout
- Health-gated rollout (SOC ≥30%, Temp ≤45°C, not CRITICAL)
- Auto-rollback if failure rate >30%
- Campaign creation wizard UI with live rollout progress

---

### Phase 6 — Root Cause Analysis Timeline (Weeks 7–8)

**Goal**: Correlate events across time to prove cause-and-effect relationships.

**Key Deliverables**:
- Cross-source event query engine (TimescaleDB + PostgreSQL)
- RCA API endpoint: `/api/v1/rca/{vehicleId}?from=&to=`
- Interactive timeline with zoom/scroll, color-coded event categories
- Click-to-expand event details

---

### Phase 7 — Observability & Monitoring (Weeks 8–9)

**Goal**: Professional-grade infrastructure monitoring.

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| Prometheus | Metrics collection | Custom Axion metrics |
| Grafana | Dashboards | 8+ monitoring panels |
| Micrometer | Spring integration | Actuator metrics exposure |
| Logback | Structured logging | JSON logs with MDC correlation IDs |

**Custom Metrics**: telemetry ingested, Kafka lag, health score distribution, active OTA campaigns, API latency (p50/p95/p99), JVM stats.

---

### Phase 8 — Polish & Presentation (Weeks 9–10)

**Key Deliverables**:
- Complete OpenAPI/Swagger documentation
- Updated README with architecture diagrams
- Single `docker-compose up -d` starts all 9–10 containers
- Load test: 100+ vehicles validated
- 10-minute structured demo script

---

## 12. Technology Stack: Minor vs Major

| Component | Minor (Done ✅) | Major (Planned 🚀) |
|-----------|----------------|---------------------|
| **State** | Redis only (120s TTL) | Redis + PostgreSQL + TimescaleDB |
| **Auth** | None | Spring Security + JWT + RBAC |
| **Frontend** | Polling (3–5s) | WebSocket (STOMP) real-time push |
| **Analytics** | Live snapshots only | 30-day trends + ML predictions |
| **ML/AI** | None | FastAPI + scikit-learn + XGBoost |
| **OTA** | Single trigger, in-memory | Campaign lifecycle, canary, rollback |
| **Monitoring** | None | Prometheus + Grafana + Actuator |
| **Logging** | Basic SLF4J | Structured JSON + MDC correlation |
| **Timeline** | None | RCA with cross-source correlation |
| **API Docs** | Minimal | Full OpenAPI/Swagger |
| **Containers** | 7 containers | 9–10 containers |

